the x squared pretty simply.

6
00:00:12,890 --> 00:00:15,150
Because there's only one
term that involves an x here.

7
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:16,950
It's only this x squared term.

8
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:18,277
So let's try to do that.

9
00:00:18,277 --> 00:00:19,360
So let me just rewrite it.

10
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:24,250
We have 2x squared
plus 3 is equal to 75.

11
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:26,610
And we're going to try to
isolate this x squared over

12
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:26,820
here.

13
00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:29,153
And the best way to do that,
or at least the first step,

14
00:00:29,153 --> 00:00:32,960
would be to subtract 3 from
both sides of this equation.

15
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:35,270
So let's subtract
3 from both sides.

16
00:00:35,270 --> 00:00:38,580
The left hand side, we're
just left with 2x squared.

17
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,690
That was the whole point of
subtracting 3 from both sides.

18
00:00:41,690 --> 00:00:46,260
And on the right hand
side, 75 minus 3 is 72.

19
00:00:46,260 --> 00:00:48,070
Now, I want to isolate
this x squared.

20
00:00:48,070 --> 00:00:49,780
I have a 2x squared here.

21
00:00:49,780 --> 00:00:51,610
So I could have just
an x squared here

22
00:00:51,610 --> 00:00:54,265
if I divide this side or
really both sides by 2.

23
00:00:54,265 --> 00:00:56,640
Anything I do to one side, I
have to do to the other side

24
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:59,370
if I want to maintain
the equality.

25
00:00:59,370 --> 00:01:01,820
So the left side, just
becomes x squared.

26
00:01:01,820 --> 00:01:06,540
And the right hand side
is 72 divided by 2 is 36.

27
00:01:06,540 --> 00:01:09,290
So we're left with x
squared is equal to 36.

28
00:01:09,290 --> 00:01:13,280
And then to solve for x,
we can take the positive,

29
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:16,720
the plus or minus square
root of both sides.

30
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:21,190
